# Bochs JIT benchmark harness

Measure interpreter vs JIT performance on the same workload.

## Build baselines

```sh
cd bochs
./configure --enable-all-optimizations --enable-show-ips --enable-x86-64 \
            --with-nogui --enable-jit --enable-cpu-level=6
make
```

Interpreter-only baseline (disable JIT at configure time):

```sh
./configure --enable-all-optimizations --enable-show-ips --enable-x86-64 \
            --with-nogui --enable-cpu-level=6
make
```

Shadow-verify build (compare JIT vs interpreter per trace):

```sh
./configure --enable-all-optimizations --enable-show-ips --enable-x86-64 \
            --with-nogui --enable-jit --enable-jit-verify --enable-cpu-level=6
make
```

## Run

Use any `.bochsrc` that boots a guest. Bochs logs IPS when `--enable-show-ips` is on.
Compare startup log lines for optimization and JIT status.

```sh
./bochs -f bench/bochsrc.txt -q
```

Record wall time and IPS from the log for:
- Integer-heavy guest loops (DOS/BIOS test or Linux `yes >/dev/null`)
- Memory copy workloads
- Full boot (optional; I/O dominated)

## Windows

Use MSYS2/MinGW or cross-config from `.conf.win64-cross-mingw32` and add
`--enable-jit` to the configure line.
